title: Benedict Cumberbatch and the Sign of Four (or is it Three?)

json.text: Hello I'm Benedict Cumberbatch,
-Did you miss me? Did you miss me? Did you miss me?
-Murray, what are you doing?
-It's not Murray, The name's MURRY-ARITY!
-Murray-arity?
-Yes! I am your arch-nemesis!
-Murray I don't really have an arch nemesis in real life.
-Well you do today, and his name is MURRAY-ARITY! Mwahahaha!
-Are you ready for my brain bending challenge, Sherlock?
-I'm not really Sherlock, I just play him on the television.
-Oh, what's your name?
-Benedict
-Well, then are you ready for my brain bending challenge Benedict-Sherlock?
-Yeah, sure what is it?
-On this table are some fruit!
-Yeah, I see you've got some apples and some oranges
-Are there more apples, or are there more oranges?
I don't know! You're the super sleuth, figure it out.
-I'm really just an actor.
-Well, act like a super sleuth and figure it out! The game is on!
-Oh, is it? Who's playing who?
-No no, not that kind of game! This game! With the fruit!
-Okay, more apples or more oranges...
I'm gonna need some help with this. -Ooh! From Watson?
-No not from Watson. From The Count
-Greetings!
-Count, how many apples are there on this table, can you count them?
-Yes. Oh of course. I love to count! There are one two three
Four luscious apples, Benedict!
-Four apples, thank you, and how many oranges are there on the table?
-There are one two three
oranges!
-Three oranges that's interesting
-Hahaha, you're stumped! You're stumped by my perplexing problem!
-No you see if there are four apples and only three oranges
Four is a bigger number than three, so that means there are more apples on the table than there are oranges!
-That is correct! Four is more than three.
- Oh drat! You win this time, Sherlock!
-Benedict.
-You win this time, Benedict-Sherlock!
-Hmm, that is ONE smart man! Hahaha...
